-- Angola’s Sonair Plans to Acquire About 51% of Sao Tome’s STP Air
-- B y   C a n d i d o   M e n d e s
-- 2012-04-09T08:18:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-09/angola-s-sonair-plans-to-acquire-about-51-of-sao-tome-s-stp-air.html
Sonair, airline unit of Sonangol EP,
will acquire a “minimum” of 51 percent of STP Air of the
islands of Sao Tome and Principe, Agencia  Angola  Press reported,
citing Prime Minister Patrice Trovoada of Sao Tome and Principe.  Sonangol, Angola’s state-run oil company, has investments
in the fuel, port and airport sectors in the islands nation and
may expand to other areas, Trovoada was cited as saying by the
Luanda-based news agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Candido Mendes in Luanda at 
